wristleft.label: Wrist Ranges of Motion Figure Table A1 page 596, Corrected with Errata March 2002: AMA Estimated Normal: Flexion (60D), Extension (60D), Ulnar Deviation (30D), Radial Deviation (20D). Motion is measured with goniometer and is reported right over left side in Degrees (D).

Actual goniometer measurements of the range of motion are only required for PR-4 (Permanent & Stationary) reports. Visual estimates of the range of motion may be adequate for Doctor's First reports and PR-2 reports.
